	(text "State Signal\n\n- PWR_LED/PSON: \n  - S0 (Working): HIGH\n  - S3 (Slpeeping): LOW\n  - S4 (Hibernation): LOW\n  - S5 (Soft Off): LOW\n\n- SLS_S4_N:\n  - S0 (Working): HIGH\n  - S3 (Slpeeping): HIGH\n  - S4 (Hibernation): LOW\n  - S5 (Soft Off): LOW"
		(exclude_from_sim no)
		(at 192.532 47.752 0)
		(effects
			(font
				(size 1.27 1.27)
			)
			(justify left)
		)
		(uuid "34630e51-abfc-48c8-8627-9b3e5b5c397e")
	)
	(text "DDI/TCP functions are defined by the BIOS firmware, \nCannot be changed in BIOS menu.\n\nBefore starting design, you should choose one of\nthe available BIOS configurations on:\nhttps://github.com/LattePandaTeam/LattePanda-Mu\n\nThe default functions are defined as follows:\n\n- DDIA: eDP 1.4b (the 40Pin connector on the Mu)\n\n- DDIB: HDMI 2.0\n\n- TCP0: HDMI 2.0\n\n- TCP1: USB TypeC (need external PD controller)"
		(exclude_from_sim no)
		(at 37.338 251.968 0)
		(effects
			(font
				(size 2.54 2.54)
			)
			(justify left)
		)
		(uuid "4790c871-c50c-44c9-8f6b-012fe110a97a")
	)
	(text "Lite Carrier has no second BIOS ROM chip welded on the board.\n~{BIOS_SEL} pull up to 3.3V to select ROM of LattePanda Mu compute module."
		(exclude_from_sim no)
		(at 395.986 270.51 0)
		(effects
			(font
				(size 1.27 1.27)
			)
			(justify left)
		)
		(uuid "58921f0f-ff2c-4945-81df-f9b4f68d0754")
	)
	(text "USB2_P6 is reserved for TypeC PD Controller\nDO NOT use it as a normal USB"
		(exclude_from_sim no)
		(at 372.11 133.604 0)
		(effects
